# Large-change execution

For large changes (multi-task implementation plans, multi-subsystem features, or work spanning several packages/files with a written plan):

- Prefer **subagent-driven development** (fresh implementer subagent per task + task review between tasks).
- Do not ask which execution style to use when a plan already exists — default to subagents unless the user says otherwise for that session.
- Keep using inline work only for small single-task fixes or when the user explicitly asks to stay in-session.
